你们应该见过很多游戏icon了，比如c站有专门做那种国产游戏图标的，我对于模型的认知和态度向来都是专模专用，就和专业的人做专业的事情是一样。

国内做欧美休闲游戏的也蛮多的，我个人也很喜欢玩休闲类的游戏，毕竟年纪大了手速跟不上了，所以特意训练了这一套Lora。

wechat：18647520807

请各位使用者注意：

此模型禁止任何形式的商业用途，仅供交流学习。

SD发展到今天其实早就应该告别抽卡时代而走向专业化了，相信再过一些时日我们就可以看出模型训练师的区别。

个人的判断标准主要是三个方面（仅供参考）：

1.泛化性：主要考研打标的严谨性和训练过程的参数判断

2.画风纯度：此标准仅限于画风lora，比如如果一个模型既2.5D又3D我就会认为训练结果的纯度不佳

3.叠用价值：我们经常会组合使用Lora，如果过程中趋于可控，那么可以判断泛用性较强，当然Lora模型的发挥会收到大模型的影响，这里仅基于训练师推荐的做判断

items.description:
This LoRA generates "crest" logos. Please google if you don't know what they look like! The model is able to produce coloured, gold, and monotone black/white by stating in the positive prompt. The LoRA usually has text in them, and I have not found a solution yet to input the text I want, except by photoshopping it out.

Thus far, the LoRA gives and produces really good results. I haven't gotten a single bad image yet. If you like a specific logo that you generated, but found that the image itself has some imperfections, simply use img2img and regenerate. This is what I experimented so far that has worked!

Also, did I mention that the img2img is really good with this LoRA! You can even draw something that you like. For instance, if you don't like the shield in the logo, just draw something that you had in mind, use img2img, insert the LoRA and "crestlora" then input the rest of the prompt. I managed to generate tons of different styles instead of the generic shield one that it produces by default.

Also, the LoRA was trained on Dreamshaper_8. Use with DPM++ SDE Karras 44 steps CFG 7

items.name: Make Good Pic XL
items.description:
Make Good Pic XL - comfy workflow

New in v1.3:

  • Great improvement in generation speed for hi-res images:

    • 25 seconds per 2K image

    • 55 seconds per 4K image
      (on 4090)

  • Fewer Custom Nodes Used

  • ToDo:

    • Find way to reduce prompt (color) bleed without slowing down generation or requiring per-prompt fine-tuning (like cut-off does).

    • Further improve image quality at higher resolutions.

New in v1.2:

  • 2K-4K high quality upscale using Mikey's custom Tiled Sampler.

    • On 4090 I get:

      • 30-40s for batch of 2x1K base images

      • 60-80s to upscale both images to 2K or 4K
        (100-120s total)

      • For now, I focused on highest quality, so generation time can probably be optimized.

  • Re-wrote much of the workflow to use fewer custom nodes.

  • Removed custom KSampler, using Mikey's instead.

  • To Do: add workflow inline comments and tips.

  • Notes:

    • It's possible Mikey's tiled sampler can be used on its own using noise instead of base image, this could potentially greatly speed up generation time of >2K images, but initial tests still unconclusive.

    • Use your preferred text-debug node if you want to see the prompts being auto-generated.

    • This workflow is intended to be open and easy to understand - using clear layout and colors with all options easily exposed in their native form.
      This makes it very easy to "reverse-engineer" and customize to any use case.

New in v1.1:

  • More control over generated images.

  • Better and more consistent image quality.

  • Simpler to use.

  • Notes added inline for better usability.

  • Simple yet effective layout with everything exposed and explained, no secrets!

  • It really does produce consistently good images - makes good use of the generate-forever checkbox.

SDXL is like old amateur radio - need to find a good frequency among the static. Usually, you can tell it is good when the workflow responds well to small changes in prompt or settings.
This workflow is such a "good frequency", with strong reception - it produces consistently good results.

Some notes about the workflow features and my experience with it and with SDXL so far:

  • Mix different XL base models on the fly - very powerful feature.

  • Add any Loras - my experience is that in most cases even very low rates like 0.2 and 0.4 are noticeable.

  • Giving a base prompt and then adding SDXL Auto-Prompter prompt can add a lot of variation with surprising and often pleasing results.

  • Generation time for me is 42 secs for batch of 2, on RTX4090.

  • Using DPM SDE Exponential for sampler is slow but produces best results in my experience, using it with low steps count gives better results than samplers with much higher steps count.

  • Upscaling using SD always loses detail for me so i don't do it, 3rd party commercial software does it better.

  • NSFW is no issue - ie no twisted nipples even with refiner.

  • Some models are better for NSFW - in my experience AltXL is the current leader in this category.

Using custom nodes and custom ksampler:

  • Mikey Custom Nodes - bash-j/mikey_nodes: comfy nodes from mikey (github.com)

  • Workflow uses ComfyUI Extreme detail control Ksampler for SDXL - v1.0 | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

  • If you haven't already, install ComfyUI manager to handle any other missing custom nodes.
    ltdrdata/ComfyUI-Manager (github.com)

items.name: Fluffy Kittens
items.description:
Fluffy cute kittens (cats get generated as well) that allow for a lot of modification (hopefully).

Trigger tokens: fyuyK4 / fyuyK4 kitten

VERSION 2.1:

This one was trained on normal SD1.5, and finetuned for better quality (v2.1) and features more tags!:

cute paws: kittens more likely to hold their front paws up

group: will generate several kittens

grey fur, brown fur, white fur: will (hopefully) generate kittens with a specified fur color

nice scenery: better backgrounds (hopefully)

in a boat: puts them in a little boat

swimming: kitten/s swimming (sometimes looking like they are drowning)

mother: kitten and her cat mother (using "fyuyK4" instead of "fyuyK4 kitten" tends to give better results)

walking: kitten walking

jumping: mid-air of kitten jumping (can look really goofy/funny)

orange fur: now added to fur color choices

looking up: makes kitten look up (hopefully)

cartoonish: added recently, this is to make this LoRA more compatible with anime/cartoon style gens. But you should set the weight of this tag down to 0.6-0.8.

CLIP SKIP?: Depends, it is generally recommended when you create anime/cartoon style images (use the "cartoonish" tag). You just have to experiment and see what works best, I got good images both with and without Clip Skip 1.

____________________________________________________________________________________________

____________________________________________________________________________________________

Version 1.0: This LoRA was trained on Dreamshaper 8, not the standard SD1.5. However, the quality of images and editability will highly depend on which model you choose. Dreamshaper 8 does not necessarily produce the best images with this LoRA. I noticed that disney style models generally perform well. Looks like Euler a, DPM++ SDE / Karras, DPM++ 2M SDE / Karras, and sometimes DDIM work well.

Trigger token: fyuyK4 kitten

Additional keywords:

cute paws: kittens more likely to hold their front paws up

group: will generate several kittens

grey fur, brown fur, white fur: will (hopefully) generate kittens with a specified fur color

orange fur: not used as a token but orange kittens were part of the training, so this generally works well.

____________________________________________________________________________________________

____________________________________________________________________________________________

By the way, in case you are curious as to how I created the dataset for this LoRA, head over to the Bing image generator and enter this:

"absolutely outstanding image of fluffy cute kitten, sitting, adorable, cute little mouth slightly open, cute paws, nice scenery"

items.name: ShadowMix
items.description:
I started combining a few models and as I added more, came up with this one. It has a lot of models I've really enjoyed such as revAnimated and cartoonish. So far, I've liked what I've created through it and I hope you do too. Is it perfect, well.....no. Hands are still a gamble, sometimes they come out great, othertimes, no. It's created some shockingly good and bad renders....it all depends on the prompts and Loras used. Works well with some and not with others so you'll have to experiment. It has a tendency to smooth out surfaces and/or objects that should be more distinct but it still creates some pretty amazing pictures. I haven't played around with it extensively so put your creative prompts out there and see what it does. I've tried simple prompts and detailed ones, both have created some great renders.

Here are some examples, some pulled from other creative geniuses:

candid photo of a captivating, alluring woman with long hair and in vintage attire, reminiscent of a bygone era, elegantly poised at a brutalist train station, waiting for transportation.
blurry, dawn, realistic lighting,
Negative prompt: cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2), grayscale

Or:

(masterpiece, top quality, best quality, official art, beautiful and aesthetic:1.2), ultra realistic, 32k, extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper, detailed background, 1girl, full body, <lora:Tingyun_v16:0.8>, tingyun, green eyes, ponytail, hair ribbon large white collar, (small fox ears:1.1), seductive smile, growling, waiting impatiently for the viewer to hurry up, (random waiting poses:1.4), (nude:1.5), medium-large breasts, thigh gap, cameltoe, cleft of venus, ass, looking at viewer, <lora:hair_length_slider_v1:1.8> <lora:CutePussy:0.6> <lora:Cameltoe:0.4> <lora:GoodHands-vanilla:1>

Or:

1girl, young girl sitting on a park bench outside in the rain, best quality, ultra-detailed, intricate, detailed face, detailed eyes, beautiful eyes, (complex lighting), cinematic lightning, solo, perfect skin, (blue eyes, round pupils), (medium-large breasts, cleavage:1.4), wet clothes, (strapless white see through dress, transparent dress:1.1), bracelets, jewelery, necklace, earrings, lakeside restaurant, lamps, (dynamic pose:1.2), (very long hair, random hairstyle), wet hair, looking at viewer, night, rain, soft lighting, glowing lights, blurry background, crowd, <lora:GodPussy1 v3:0.3> <lora:Cameltoe:0.4>  <lyco:ShinyOiledSkin_v20-LyCORIS:0.4> <lora:pokies_9:0.5> <lora:transparent_dress:0.8>

For faces, I HIGHLY recommend adetailer. I will usually put something like "detailed face, long eyelashes, blush, lipstick, perfecteyes eyes, <lora:perfecteyes:1>"
